history.content: For SWE, 186 definitely. If you're more into data-related roles, then maybe Data 100 but tbh the only useful skill 100 teaches you is pandas, which can be self-learnt quite easily. On the other hand, 186 most crucially teaches you how to wrestle with a large Java codebase, which is definitely more useful going into industry in any SWE position.

I was hoping someone could explain to me from a software engineering perspective, which class is better for industry and making more money. I know I'll be taking one of them and self studying the other, but I've heard that 186 is an incredibly boring class and mostly theory that isn't relevant, but I've also heard that it's great for learning about database systems which are also really good for industry. If someone could clarify, I would really appreciate that. Thank you.
history.subject: Better for industry 186 vs Data 100
